#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Iterative-./ai test scenario: pizza ordering + table reservations.

This playbook extends ``skel-test-pizzeria-orders`` to exercise the
built-in per-service ``./ai`` agent's *iterative refactor capability*.
The scenario builds on top of the completed pizzeria application: it
generates the same FastAPI + React + Flutter wrapper, verifies the
pizzeria flow passes, then asks ``./ai`` to add a table reservation
system to the backend and verifies BOTH the original pizzeria flow
(regression) AND the new reservation flow (V_reservation) are green.

Naming convention mirrors the existing playbook: the wrapper lands at
``_test_projects/test-pizza-reservation/`` (separate from the
``test-pizzeria-orders`` checkout so the two scenarios never collide on
disk).

Phase outline::

    Phase 0: Pre-flight (Ollama reachable, models pulled).
    Phase 1: Generate the pizzeria wrapper from scratch (same prompts
             as the pizzeria playbook).
    Phase 2: Start backend + run baseline V_pizza (14-step HTTP) so we
             KNOW the starting state is healthy. If this fails, the
             generated app is broken and there's no point asking ./ai
             to refactor it.
    Phase 3: ``git init`` the wrapper so ./ai apply has a clean tree to
             diff against (the safety contract refuses dirty trees).
    Phase 4: Invoke ``./ai orders_api apply <RESERVATION_PROMPT>``.
             This is the iterative agent step — ./ai runs the LM,
             applies file diffs, runs the service's own ``./test``
             command, and loops with a fix model until tests pass (or
             ``--fix-timeout-m`` is reached).
    Phase 5: Restart the backend (./ai may have introduced new tables
             or settings) and re-run V_pizza. The agent prompt asks
             explicitly for the pizza ordering contract to remain
             intact, so this MUST be green.
    Phase 6: Run V_reservation — POST a reservation with valid date +
             time, persist + retrieve, then assert the server rejects
             requests with missing or malformed date/time.

Exit codes::

    0  every check passed (V_pizza baseline + regression + V_reservation)
    1  at least one assertion failed
    2  toolchain missing or Ollama unreachable (setup skip)

Wrapper is kept on disk with ``--keep`` for post-mortem inspection.
"""

